class="comment-text"> <span
class="date">Mon 21st Nov 2011 at 8:47 am</span><p>I am somewhat skeptical towards these management techniques. They all tend to suffer from the Hawthrone effect (google it).</p><p>I&#8217;ve been in a lot of projects that would have been doomed according to these experts and in fact devlivered straight on time, and also a few which didn&#8217;t in spite in of being buzzword compliant.</p><p>Don&#8217;t get me wrong here, some of these techniques are perfectly fine but they&#8217;re not a in themselves a ticket to success. A lot of things are more important, like competent people and even more so listening to said competent people, and these things are by nature harder to quantify.</p><p>One thing I do know, and if I would write a book one day it would be about that, is that the people actually working in the project can tell quite early on if they think it&#8217;s a dead end project or not. Knowing why they think that and how to draw from their previous experiences would do much more for your project than following any book.</p> <span
